olved happen to be complicated interactions between many molecular machines, those two words are sufficient. Yet, if you don&#39;t understand those things the question becomes too broad and you&#39;d be better off reading some &quot;Kinetics/Biophysics/Thermodynamics for dummies&quot; textbook."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/Yiloe.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":8218,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/8218/jason-c","reputation":423,"display_name":"Jason C"},"score":1,"post_id":41989,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/LVigb.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":13338,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/13338/eli-korvigo","reputation":548,"display_name":"Eli Korvigo","accept_rate":100},"edited":false,"creation_date":1451866636,"comment_id":71545,"body":"Damn. It&#39;s like <a href=\"https://youtu.be/MO0r930Sn_8\" rel=\"nofollow\">that video of Feynman explaining magnetism<\/a>. Guess I&#39;m <i>that<\/i> guy."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/LVigb.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":13338,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/13338/eli-korvigo","reputation":548,"display_name":"Eli Korvigo","accept_rate":100},"score":1,"post_id":41989,"edited":false,"creation_date":1451866640,"comment_id":71546,"body":"<a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/860989\" rel=\"nofollow\">This<\/a>, while requiring some prior knowledge, will get you started. Refer to wiki for additional information while reading the paper."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/aedf04941d1a31e7e252c36f2cf95a46?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":20732,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/20732/the-nate","reputation":145,"display_name":"The Nate"},"score":1,"post_id":41989,"edited":false,"creation_date":1451897440,"comment_id":71562,"body":"As Feynman said, though, it is a great question. He wasn&#39;