\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/dyJNX.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>Anteater do not camouflage (for predation purpose) when they predate ants<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/YPhv4.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/YPhv4.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>The Mandarinfish is also poorly camouflaged and predates on harpacticoid copepods, polychaete worms, small gastropods, gammaridean amphipods, fish eggs and ostracods.<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/D1BL0.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/D1BL0.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>As @AMR suggested in the comments, humans are poorly camouflaged too.<\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/cOPTb.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/cOPTb.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/a><\/p>\n","answer_id":42378,"question_id":42376,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1453047461},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b10de963b115fd0720d6a558fd1ac06c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":10456,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/10456/march-ho","reputation":5867,"display_name":"March Ho","accept_rate":80},"score":4,"is_accepted":false,"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1452900959,"creation_date":1452900959,"body":"<p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poison_dart_frog\" rel=\"nofollow\">Poison dart frogs<\/a> have <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aposematism\" rel=\"nofollow\">aposematic colouration<\/a>, making them the exact opposite of camoflaged. <\/p>\n\n<p>They are also predators, since they <a href=\"http://animals.nationalgeographic.com/animals/amphibians/poison-frog/\" rel=\"nofollow\">feed on<\/a> ants, termites and beetles. <\/p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/KpdDJm.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/KpdDJm.j