al the blood pressure in the brachial artery?<\/p>\n\n<p>I've heard it does, but it doesn't quite seem to make sense as I'd think the blood pressure would be lowered the further it travels?<\/p>\n","question_id":38805,"tags":["human-biology","physiology","human-anatomy","cardiology"],"score":2,"down_vote_count":1,"is_answered":true,"view_count":73,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1451408762},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/32a2a5a118997c527032406f3b843f9d?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":18708,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/18708/m-beausoleil","reputation":88,"display_name":"M. Beausoleil","accept_rate":50},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1sIMq.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4108,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4108/remi-b","reputation":22909,"display_name":"Remi.b","accept_rate":88},"score":2,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/32a2a5a118997c527032406f3b843f9d?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":18708,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/18708/m-beausoleil","reputation":88,"display_name":"M. Beausoleil","accept_rate":50},"score":0,"post_id":42377,"edited":false,"creation_date":1452973416,"comment_id":72836,"body":"Do you have a reference to this? I mean, is this a quote? Is it like the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gene_signature\" rel=\"nofollow\">gene signature<\/a> or the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genomic_signature\" rel=\"nofollow\">genomic signature<\/a>?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1sIMq.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4108,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4108/remi-b","reputation":22909,"display_name":"Remi.b","accept_rate":88},"score":1,"post_id":42377,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/32a2a5a118997c527032406f3b843f