aph.facebook.com/100003301550273/picture?type=large","user_type":"registered","user_id":5700,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5700/user4147","reputation":856,"display_name":"user4147","accept_rate":56},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5cff3e84bcedd40163c74d33b827ac7c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":307,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/307/lancelafontaine","reputation":3814,"display_name":"LanceLafontaine","accept_rate":47},"score":0,"post_id":20375,"edited":false,"creation_date":1407690012,"comment_id":30582,"body":"This question is a near-duplicate of <a href=\"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/1054/what-causes-fingerprints-to-form-and-why-is-the-pattern-formed-unique\" title=\"what causes fingerprints to form and why is the pattern formed unique\">biology.stackexchange.com/questions/1054/&hellip;<\/a>"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/jlp4Q.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":5198,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5198/anongoodnurse","reputation":12148,"display_name":"anongoodnurse"},"score":3,"post_id":20375,"edited":false,"creation_date":1423895751,"comment_id":47058,"body":"It&#39;s considered appropriate on biology.se that you present some of your reading/research with your question. Have you read anything about the formation of fingerprints? Otherwise it will be closed."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/ZR6SM.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":5005,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5005/hello-there-andy","reputation":1616,"display_name":"hello_there_andy","accept_rate":69},"score":1,"post_id":20375,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/jlp4Q.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":5198,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5198/anongoodnurse","reputation":12148,"display_name":"anongoodnurse"},"edited":false,"creation_date":